WorldStage Newsonline– Nigeria’s National Economic Council chaired by Vice President Yemi Osinbajo, SAN at its monthly meeting on Thursday was updated by the Minister of Finance on the balance in the Excess Crude Account (ECA) which she put at $1,918,509,918. 86 as at July 16, 2018. She also reported to the Council that the balance in the Excess Crude Account (ECA) as at July 16, 2018 stands at $1,918,509,918. 86 The current balance in the Stabilization Account as at July 16, 2018 stands at N18,892,864,216.65. The current balance in the Natural Resources Development Fund as July 16, 2018  stands at N133,715,427,387.37.